  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt at restitution by paying back part of the funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the guidelines for non-violent property crimes of this scale typically involve shorter custodial sentences or probation. A ten-year sentence, as suggested by the spectator, is disproportionately punitive and legally inconsistent with standard sentencing practices for $25,000, which often aim for rehabilitation and repayment rather than long-term incarceration. An eight-month sentence balances the gravity of the crime against the defendant's lack of prior record.",
  "verdict": 8
